The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Nov. 21 (PTI): Mumbai police arrested builder Yusuf Lakdawala on Thursday night for allegedly threatening actress Sadhana and barging into her house in August this year.           
	Lakdawala was later granted bail by a magistrates court, the police said. Sadhana, 68, had lodged a complaint alleging that Lakdawala had threatened to kill her if she did not vacate her house in Santacruz.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Four persons, including a woman hailing from Bangladesh, were arrested in west Delhi for allegedly cheating people by luring them into exchanging dollars with Indian currency at very cheap rates, police said. The gang used to target owners of medicine and mobile shops.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A man allegedly involved in a theft of Rs 1 crore from the home of a builder in south Delhi was arrested from Uttar Pradesh while the main accused is still on the run, police said. Ram Kishore, 25, a domestic help, had allegedly fled from Sunil Kumar Bedis home with Rs 1 crore on November 14 when they were away.                  
	 Nagpur (PTI): A deputy education officer with zilla parishad in Nagpur has been arrested for allegedly demanding and accepting a bribe of Rs 25,000 from a schoolteacher, police said on Sunday.                   
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A 27-year-old man was charred to death and his wife sustained burn injuries when their car caught fire on Saturday on the Delhi-Dehra Dun national highway in Muzaffarnagar, police said. Pranay Kumar Jain and his wife, Samata, were on their way to Delhi from Saharanpur when their car collided with a cemented pipe and caught fire.                  
	 Udhagamandalam, (PTI): A 60-year-old man was trampled to death and his wife injured when a herd of elephants attacked them at an estate near Udhagamandalam in Tamil Nadu on Sunday.                                                                                                                                              
